I recommend timing it with your phone, or just going for as long as you can if you don't have the wherewithall to manage that. There's an actual science to how this resets your HPA axis. Works much better and more immediately than drugs in a lot of scenarios, once you get good at it. Takes practice to do well, and best to try when you aren't in crisis so you can get the hang of it.

Eliade 5/20/2022 8:43 AM
@Deleted User Because qualitative content is differently accessible to each person, it's beneficial for empirical work to try and develop a method for any interested party to cultivate a set of contents. Even within my own life, it's hard to remember what it was like to be depressed so many years back. In the midst of an emotion, the accessibility of so many others disappears, and so too does the possibility of the interesting constructs that build off of them. Is 'All This Real' talks about various religious traditions that cultivate imagery and feeling to extraordinary degrees that a layman might dismiss out of hand, and tries to allay an egocentric bias. But my comedic answer is that it's all real, everything. You can't find something that's fake. (edited)
